[{"id":"VR914707","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows an interference pattern titled Central Bright Fringe. The pattern is comprised of 35 alternating black and white small rectangles of equal size. Distance D indicated below the pattern begins at approximately the 8th rectangle, which is the 4th white rectangle, and stops at approximately the 28th rectangle, which is the 14th white rectangle. The Central Bright Fringe is indicated by an arrow pointing at the 18th rectangle, which is the 9th white rectangle.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR914707.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Monochromatic light of wavelength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda\"><math alttext=\"lambda\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>λ</mi></math></span></span> is incident upon a double slit. The figure shows the resulting interference pattern on a screen that is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>L</mi></math></span></span> away from the slits, and the distance between the two indicated maxima is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>D</mi></math></span></span>. What is the distance between the two slits?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR914707_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator lambda L, and denominator D\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator lambda L, and denominator D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mi>D</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 times, the fraction with numerator lambda L, and denominator D, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"2 times, the fraction with numerator lambda L, and denominator D, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mi>D</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"5 times, the fraction with numerator lambda L, and denominator D, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"5 times, the fraction with numerator lambda L, and denominator D, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>5</mn><mfrac><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mi>D</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 times, the fraction with numerator lambda L, and denominator D, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"10 times, the fraction with numerator lambda L, and denominator D, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn><mfrac><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mi>D</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]